Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core
and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the pepper and @sweet potato{300%g}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle
with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over half the
@mexican style spice mix{2}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}. Put half the black
beans in a #bowl{} and mash with a #fork{} or #masher{} until broken up.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot,
add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and remaining Mexican style spice mix.
Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @water{100%ml}, @vegetable stock paste{10} and black beans (whole and
crushed).

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the sauce has
thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While the beans simmer, zest the @lime{1} and cut into wedges.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

About 3 mins before the sweet potatoes and peppers are ready, cook the
@basmati rice{1}(steamed) according to pack instructions.

When cooked, transfer the rice to a bowl and stir through the lime zest.

Reheat the beans if necessary.

Add a splash of water if they're a little dry. Taste and add salt and pepper if
needed.

Divide the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the refried beans, roasted sweet potatoes and peppers.

Add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}, then finish with the grated cheese and
spring onion.

Serve with the lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!